Source: I002 and `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-17-profile-refresh-transaction.md`, Task 5.

Delete `fetchGrok`, `grokGet`, `finishGrokPart`, and all transient live-profile `grok*` transaction fields after the shared transaction path is authoritative.

Acceptance: Grok uses one token for both legs, completes exactly once in either order, preserves monthly-only partial success/auth/backoff behaviour, records each exchange once, and leaves no Grok transaction state on profiles.